HEADWORD: Seven-shooter
<hw>Sev"en-shoot`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A firearm,
esp. a pistol, with seven barrels or chambers for cartridges, or one
capable of firing seven shots without reloading.</def>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Seventeen</ent>⟦br⟧
